          translation: "I take refuge in Your form that destroys all afflictions -- adorned with armlets, bracelets, bangles and magnificent rings set with great gems on Your four resplendent arms that hold the mace, conch, discus and lotus; Your waist graced by a golden girdle over a shining yellow silk garment, and Your feet radiant as spotless lotuses.",
          commentary: "This verse completes the description of the Lord's form from the arms downward. The four arms of Vishnu hold His characteristic emblems -- the mace (gada), conch (shankha), discus (cakra/ari), and lotus (pankeruha). The poet notes each ornament meticulously: keyura (upper armlets), angada (shoulder ornaments), kankana (bangles), and anguliya (rings). The verse ends with the devotee's declaration of taking refuge in this affliction-destroying form.",
