          translation: "Delighted in mind by the praises of the great sages, shining with Your most magnificent form and spotless glory, You returned to Your own abode, O Slayer of Madhu, revelling in bliss! O Lord of Guruvayur, please destroy all my diseases!",
          commentary: "The closing verse follows Bhattathiri's signature pattern: the cosmic narrative resolves into personal prayer. The victorious Lord, pleased by sages' praises (stavana-mukharaih modita-mana), returns to Vaikuntha in full glory. The compound 'sukha-rasa-vihari' (one who revels in the essence of bliss) captures the Lord's nature — all this cosmic drama is effortless joy for Him. The final plea 'nirundhya rogam me sakalam' (destroy all my diseases) draws a parallel: as the Lord rescued the Earth from drowning, may He rescue Bhattathiri from illness.",
